<h2><b>ADULTS</b></h2>
<p><b> </b></p>
<p><b><b>
<h4><a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/life-learning/spiritual-life-classes/exploring-the-book-of-acts/">EXPLORING THE BOOK OF ACTS</a></h4>
</b><strong><i>7:00-8:30 PM in the Chapel</i></strong><br /></b>"But you will receive power when the Holy Spirit comes on you; and you will be my witnesses in Jerusalem, and all Judea, and Samaria and to the ends of the earth."<br /><br />Come learn in detail how the Holy Spirit worked and moved through the lives of the Apostles, and in extension, His people today. Rev. Rod Rider pulls from biblical, historical, and scholarly sources to bring us surprising insights from the book of Acts.</p>
<p><b><br /></b></p>
<p><b><a><b> </b></a>
<h4><a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/life-learning/spiritual-life-classes/ladies-tuesday-am-bible-study/"><b>LADIES' BIBLE STUDY</b></a></h4>
</b></p>
<p><b><em><strong>7:00-8:30 PM in the Hospitality Center</strong><br /></em></b><em>Interruptions.</em>They're aggravating.  Sometimes infuriating. But how we handle interruptions actually tell us more about  ourselves. <em>Jonah: Navigating a Life Interrupted</em> provides a personal  study experience five days a week in this in-depth women's Bible study.  In 7 sessions, Priscilla redefines interruption and shows that  interruption is actually God's invitation to do something beyond our  wildest dreams. When Jonah was willing to allow God to interrupt his  life, the result was revival in an entire city. Led by Ingrid Roland</p>
<p><b><br /></b></p>
<p><b><a><b> </b></a>
<h4><a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/get-connected/men/mens-bible-studies/"><b>MEN'S BIBLE STUDY</b></a></h4>
<strong><em>7:00-8:30 PM in Room 221</em></strong><br /></b><b><em><strong>&nbsp;</strong></em></b>Our current series, <em>The Essence of Prayer</em>, will help all men to understand, experience, and  practice prayer in its many forms. Learn how prayer can move you inward into personal  transformation,  upward toward intimacy with God, and outward to minister  to others.  You'll be led beyond questions to a deeper understanding and  practice  of prayer, bringing you closer to God, to yourself, and to your   community.</p>
<p><b><br /></b></p>
<p><b>
<h4><b><a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/life-learning/spiritual-life-classes/alpha-course/">ALPHA COURSE</a><br /></b></h4>
<strong><i>7:00-8:30 PM in Room 221</i></strong></b><i><br /></i>&ldquo;Is there more to life?" What am I doing here?" "Is this it?" Do you ever find yourself asking questions like these? If so...find out more, with the Alpha Course: explore the meaning of life. Alpha is an opportunity to explore the meaning of life in a relaxed, friendly setting where no question about life or God is seen as too simple or too hostile...all are welcome. Led by Pastor Joel Slater.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><b>
<h4><b><a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/life-learning/family-life-classes/different-children-different-needs/">DIFFERENT CHILDREN, DIFFERENT NEEDS</a><br /></b></h4>
<strong><i>7:00-8:30 PM in Rooms 229-230</i></strong></b><i><br />Material Fee: $20.00 for individual; $35.00 for couple</i><br />The key to effective parenting is discovering what motivates your child to respond the way he or she does. Different Children Different Needs is one of those &ldquo;Ah ha&rdquo; classes that gives you practical answers to dealing with all of your relationships, but particularly as it relates to your children.&nbsp; Through the use of the scientific diagnostic, the DiSC profile, we will go on one of the most enlightening journeys of your life. Tied into the teaching are plenty of practical Love and Logic tools to handle any unique temperament in powerful and positive ways! Led by Linda Noah and Amy Slater.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><b>
<h4><b><a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/get-connected/music-and-worship/portland-christian-center-choir/">PORTLAND CHRISTIAN CENTER CHOIR</a><br /></b></h4>
<strong><i>7:00-8:30 PM in the Choir Room</i></strong></b><i><br /></i>The Portland Christian Center Choir is open periodically for new members. If you are at least 18 years of age, and have music experience, we'd love to have you audition to join us!</p>
<p><b><br /></b></p>
