<h2><b><b>CHILDREN</b></b></h2>
<p><strong><a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/kidsmusic/">
<h4></h4>
</a>
<h4><a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/kidsmusic/">KIDS PRAISE COMPANY! - CHILDREN 1ST-5TH GRADES</a></h4>
</strong><em><strong>6:00-7:00 PM IN ROOMS 217-219</strong></em><br />Kids, join us for the most awesome children's choir on the planet -  Kids Praise Company! This super fun and musically educational program is for all kids from 1st-5th grades. Join us as we have tons of fun launching into our spring musical. This fully staged, costumed and coreographed event is sure to be one of the highlights of your year! You don't want to miss it!!</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4><a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/get-connected/children/midweek-programs/nursery/">NURSERY CARE - CHILDREN BIRTH-AGE 2</a></h4>
<p><em><strong>7:00-8:30 PM in the Nursery</strong></em><br />We have loving, CPR-trained, background checked nursery workers to provide tender care to your little ones while mom and dad attend a class or workshop.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4><a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/get-connected/children/midweek-programs/preschool/">RAINBOWS CLUB - CHILDREN AGE 3-PRE K</a></h4>
<p><em><strong>7:00-8:30 PM</strong></em><br />Join us each week for a fun adventure aboard Noah's Ark! We earn a different animal  badge each month by attending class, memorizing a bible verse and doing  fun worksheets and crafts.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4><a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/get-connected/children/midweek-programs/elementary/">ROYAL RANGERS - BOYS K-5TH GRADE</a></h4>
<p><em><strong>7:00-8:30 PM</strong></em><br />Royal Rangers offers character and servant leadership education to boys and young men in a highly relational, fun, and interactive environment, similar to Boy Scouts.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4><a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/get-connected/children/midweek-programs/elementary/">M'S GIRLS CLUB - GIRLS K-5TH GRADE</a></h4>
<p><em><strong>7:00-8:30 PM</strong></em><br />M's Club guides girls in their relationship with Jesus through an environment of support, friendship, crafts and activities, while helping them develop their unique gifts and abilities.</p>
